# This is a managed Expo project — ios/ and android/ are never
# committed, they're generated fresh by `expo prebuild` on every EAS
# build. @expo/fingerprint's "bareNativeDir" heuristic detects a
# physically-present ios/ directory at hash time and includes its
# contents as a fingerprint source, but PREBUILD runs before the
# runtime-version fingerprint is calculated on EAS's build workers,
# while the local `eas build` invocation runs before any prebuild —
# so the same project produces two different fingerprints purely from
# this ordering difference, with no real native config change behind
# it. Excluding the generated directories keeps the fingerprint
# derived from what actually determines native output (app.json,
# package.json, plugin config), consistent on both sides.
ios/**
android/**
